HOUSTON – Following its acquisition by PWA Inc. , the new combined entity, ProSep, is investing over $2 million in new headquarters and laboratories in Houston. The company has invested in two new sites totaling 28,000 sq ft (2,601 sq m) featuring offices, a laboratory, and a warehouse. ProSep provides integrated process separation solutions to the global oil and gas industry.   It has operations in the UK and Malaysia and employs over 95 people. The company says is looking to expand its global operations in key regions including North America, South America, the Middle East, Europe, and Asia Pacific. 